                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Regular, by trained hand.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra Giyorgis. Gabra
                        Giyorgis (s. Additio 1). The same scribe wrote KY-068.<date>Late 19th
                           century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the Emperor, Patriarch and
                           Metropolitan; headings and incipits (occasionally initial words) of the
                           constituent texts; the words ቡራኬ፡, እማሬ፡ and እገሌ፡; abbreviations; elements
                           of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals; musical notation.
                           
 On fol. 4r, a few lines are rubricated (in groups of two lines,
                           alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
