               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0171KY">Koholo Yoḥannǝs Dabra Betel / KY</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1881" notAfter="1889">
                        <locus target="#8rb">8rb</locus>: Yoḥannǝs is mentioned as the reigning
                        monarch. <locus target="#37ra">37ra-</locus>rb: Ṗeṭros is mentioned as the
                        Patriarch of Alexandria and another Ṗeṭros as the Metropolitan of Ethiopia
                        (the scribe may have committed a mistake while writing in the Patriarch’s
                        name). <locus target="#29va">29va</locus>: Ṗeṭros is mentioned as the
                        Metropolitan, while the space for the name of the Patriarch is left vacant.
                           <locus target="#54rb">54rb</locus>: Qerǝllos is mentioned as the
                        Patriarch of Alexandria. Yoḥannǝs IV was Emperor of Ethiopia in 1872-89.
                        Cyril V was Patriarch of Alexandria in 1874-1927. Ṗeṭros IV was Metropolitan
                        of Ethiopia in 1881-1917.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>fitawrari Gabra Takla Hāymānot (s. Additio
                     2). Also mentioned is his wife wayzaro
                     ʾAbärraš and other relatives. His name has been also added into the
                     supplication formulas or interlineally throughout the Ms.</provenance></history>
